41AuraApplication::AuraApplication(Unit* target, Unit* caster, Aura* aura, uint8 effMask):
42_target(target), _base(aura), _removeMode(AURA_REMOVE_NONE), _slot(MAX_AURAS),
43_flags(AFLAG_NONE), _effectsToApply(effMask), _needClientUpdate(false)
44{
45 ASSERT(GetTarget() && GetBase());
46
47 if (GetBase()->CanBeSentToClient())
48 {
49 // Try find slot for aura
50 uint8 slot = MAX_AURAS;
51 // Lookup for auras already applied from spell
52 if (AuraApplication * foundAura = GetTarget()->GetAuraApplication(GetBase()->GetId(), GetBase()->GetCasterGUID(), GetBase()->GetCastItemGUID()))
53 {
54 // allow use single slot only by auras from same caster
55 slot = foundAura->GetSlot();
56 }
57 else
58 {
59 Unit::VisibleAuraMap const* visibleAuras = GetTarget()->GetVisibleAuras();
60 // lookup for free slots in units visibleAuras
61 Unit::VisibleAuraMap::const_iterator itr = visibleAuras->find(0);
62 for (uint32 freeSlot = 0; freeSlot < MAX_AURAS; ++itr, ++freeSlot)
63 {
64 if (itr == visibleAuras->end() || itr->first != freeSlot)
65 {
66 slot = freeSlot;
67 break;
68 }
69 }
70 }
71
72 // Register Visible Aura
73 if (slot < MAX_AURAS)
74 {
75 _slot = slot;
76 GetTarget()->SetVisibleAura(slot, this);
77 SetNeedClientUpdate();
78 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Aura: %u Effect: %d put to unit visible auras slot: %u", GetBase()->GetId(), GetEffectMask(), slot);
79 }
80 else
81 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Aura: %u Effect: %d could not find empty unit visible slot", GetBase()->GetId(), GetEffectMask());
82 }
83
84 _InitFlags(caster, effMask);
85}
86
87void AuraApplication::_Remove()
88{
89 uint8 slot = GetSlot();
90
91 if (slot >= MAX_AURAS)
92 return;
93
94 if (AuraApplication * foundAura = _target->GetAuraApplication(GetBase()->GetId(), GetBase()->GetCasterGUID(), GetBase()->GetCastItemGUID()))
95 {
96 // Reuse visible aura slot by aura which is still applied - prevent storing dead pointers
97 if (slot == foundAura->GetSlot())
98 {
99 if (GetTarget()->GetVisibleAura(slot) == this)
100 {
101 GetTarget()->SetVisibleAura(slot, foundAura);
102 foundAura->SetNeedClientUpdate();
103 }
104 // set not valid slot for aura - prevent removing other visible aura
105 slot = MAX_AURAS;
106 }
107 }
108
109 // update for out of range group members
110 if (slot < MAX_AURAS)
111 {
112 GetTarget()->RemoveVisibleAura(slot);
113 ClientUpdate(true);
114 }
115}

117void AuraApplication::_InitFlags(Unit* caster, uint8 effMask)
118{
119 // mark as selfcast if needed
120 _flags |= (GetBase()->GetCasterGUID() == GetTarget()->GetGUID()) ? AFLAG_CASTER : AFLAG_NONE;
121
122 // aura is cast by self or an enemy
123 // one negative effect and we know aura is negative
124 if (IsSelfcast() || !caster || !caster->IsFriendlyTo(GetTarget()))
125 {
126 bool negativeFound = false;
127 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
128 {
129 if (((1<<i) & effMask) && !GetBase()->GetSpellInfo()->IsPositiveEffect(i))
130 {
131 negativeFound = true;
132 break;
133 }
134 }
135 _flags |= negativeFound ? AFLAG_NEGATIVE : AFLAG_POSITIVE;
136 }
137 // aura is cast by friend
138 // one positive effect and we know aura is positive
139 else
140 {
141 bool positiveFound = false;
142 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
143 {
144 if (((1<<i) & effMask) && GetBase()->GetSpellInfo()->IsPositiveEffect(i))
145 {
146 positiveFound = true;
147 break;
148 }
149 }
150 _flags |= positiveFound ? AFLAG_POSITIVE : AFLAG_NEGATIVE;
151 }
152}
153
154void AuraApplication::_HandleEffect(uint8 effIndex, bool apply)
155{
156 AuraEffect* aurEff = GetBase()->GetEffect(effIndex);
157 ASSERT(aurEff);
158 ASSERT(HasEffect(effIndex) == (!apply));
159 ASSERT((1<<effIndex) & _effectsToApply);
160 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "AuraApplication::_HandleEffect: %u, apply: %u: amount: %u", aurEff->GetAuraType(), apply, aurEff->GetAmount());
161
162 if (apply)
163 {
164 ASSERT(!(_flags & (1<<effIndex)));
165 _flags |= 1<<effIndex;
166 aurEff->HandleEffect(this, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL, true);
167 }
168 else
169 {
170 ASSERT(_flags & (1<<effIndex));
171 _flags &= ~(1<<effIndex);
172 aurEff->HandleEffect(this, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL, false);
173
174 // Remove all triggered by aura spells vs unlimited duration
175 aurEff->CleanupTriggeredSpells(GetTarget());
176 }
177 SetNeedClientUpdate();
178}
179
180void AuraApplication::BuildUpdatePacket(ByteBuffer& data, bool remove) const
181{
182 data << uint8(_slot);
183
184 if (remove)
185 {
186 ASSERT(!_target->GetVisibleAura(_slot));
187 data << uint32(0);
188 return;
189 }
190 ASSERT(_target->GetVisibleAura(_slot));
191
192 Aura const* aura = GetBase();
193 data << uint32(aura->GetId());
194 uint32 flags = _flags;
195 if (aura->GetMaxDuration() > 0 && !aura->GetSpellInfo()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_HIDE_DURATION))
196 flags |= AFLAG_DURATION;
197 data << uint8(flags);
198 data << uint8(aura->GetCasterLevel());
199 // send stack amount for aura which could be stacked (never 0 - causes incorrect display) or charges
200 // stack amount has priority over charges (checked on retail with spell 50262)
201 data << uint8(aura->GetSpellInfo()->StackAmount ? aura->GetStackAmount() : aura->GetCharges());
202
203 if (!(flags & AFLAG_CASTER))
204 data << aura->GetCasterGUID().WriteAsPacked();
205
206 if (flags & AFLAG_DURATION)
207 {
208 data << uint32(aura->GetMaxDuration());
209 data << uint32(aura->GetDuration());
210 }
211}

213void AuraApplication::ClientUpdate(bool remove)
214{
215 _needClientUpdate = false;
216
217 WorldPacket data(SMSG_AURA_UPDATE);
218 data << GetTarget()->GetPackGUID();
219 BuildUpdatePacket(data, remove);
220
221 _target->SendMessageToSet(&data, true);
222}

224uint8 Aura::BuildEffectMaskForOwner(SpellInfo const* spellProto, uint8 avalibleEffectMask, WorldObject* owner)
225{
226 ASSERT(spellProto);
227 ASSERT(owner);
228 uint8 effMask = 0;
229 switch (owner->GetTypeId())
230 {
231 case TYPEID_UNIT:
232 case TYPEID_PLAYER:
233 for (uint8 i = 0; i< MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
234 {
235 if (spellProto->Effects[i].IsUnitOwnedAuraEffect())
236 effMask |= 1 << i;
237 }
238 break;
239 case TYPEID_DYNAMICOBJECT:
240 for (uint8 i = 0; i< MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
241 {
242 if (spellProto->Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA)
243 effMask |= 1 << i;
244 }
245 break;
246 default:
247 break;
248 }
249 return effMask & avalibleEffectMask;
250}

252Aura* Aura::TryRefreshStackOrCreate(SpellInfo const* spellproto, uint8 tryEffMask, WorldObject* owner, Unit* caster, int32* baseAmount /*= NULL*/, Item* castItem /*= NULL*/, ObjectGuid casterGUID /*= ObjectGuid::Empty*/, bool* refresh /*= NULL*/)
253{
254 ASSERT(spellproto);
255 ASSERT(owner);
256 ASSERT(caster || casterGUID);
257 ASSERT(tryEffMask <= MAX_EFFECT_MASK);
258 if (refresh)
259 *refresh = false;
260 uint8 effMask = Aura::BuildEffectMaskForOwner(spellproto, tryEffMask, owner);
261 if (!effMask)
262 return NULL;
263 if (Aura* foundAura = owner->ToUnit()->_TryStackingOrRefreshingExistingAura(spellproto, effMask, caster, baseAmount, castItem, casterGUID))
264 {
265 // we've here aura, which script triggered removal after modding stack amount
266 // check the state here, so we won't create new Aura object
267 if (foundAura->IsRemoved())
268 return NULL;
269
270 if (refresh)
271 *refresh = true;
272 return foundAura;
273 }
274 else
275 return Create(spellproto, effMask, owner, caster, baseAmount, castItem, casterGUID);
276}

278Aura* Aura::TryCreate(SpellInfo const* spellproto, uint8 tryEffMask, WorldObject* owner, Unit* caster, int32* baseAmount /*= NULL*/, Item* castItem /*= NULL*/, ObjectGuid casterGUID /*= ObjectGuid::Empty*/)
279{
280 ASSERT(spellproto);
281 ASSERT(owner);
282 ASSERT(caster || casterGUID);
283 ASSERT(tryEffMask <= MAX_EFFECT_MASK);
284 uint8 effMask = Aura::BuildEffectMaskForOwner(spellproto, tryEffMask, owner);
285 if (!effMask)
286 return NULL;
287 return Create(spellproto, effMask, owner, caster, baseAmount, castItem, casterGUID);
288}
289
290Aura* Aura::Create(SpellInfo const* spellproto, uint8 effMask, WorldObject* owner, Unit* caster, int32* baseAmount, Item* castItem, ObjectGuid casterGUID)
291{
292 ASSERT(effMask);
293 ASSERT(spellproto);
294 ASSERT(owner);
295 ASSERT(caster || casterGUID);
296 ASSERT(effMask <= MAX_EFFECT_MASK);
297 // try to get caster of aura
298 if (casterGUID)
299 {
300 if (owner->GetGUID() == casterGUID)
301 caster = owner->ToUnit();
302 else
303 caster = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*owner, casterGUID);
304 }
305 else
306 casterGUID = caster->GetGUID();
307
308 // check if aura can be owned by owner
309 if (owner->isType(TYPEMASK_UNIT))
310 if (!owner->IsInWorld() || ((Unit*)owner)->IsDuringRemoveFromWorld())
311 // owner not in world so don't allow to own not self cast single target auras
312 if (casterGUID != owner->GetGUID() && spellproto->IsSingleTarget())
313 return NULL;
314
315 Aura* aura = NULL;
316 switch (owner->GetTypeId())
317 {
318 case TYPEID_UNIT:
319 case TYPEID_PLAYER:
320 aura = new UnitAura(spellproto, effMask, owner, caster, baseAmount, castItem, casterGUID);
321 break;
322 case TYPEID_DYNAMICOBJECT:
323 aura = new DynObjAura(spellproto, effMask, owner, caster, baseAmount, castItem, casterGUID);
324 break;
325 default:
326 ABORT();
327 return NULL;
328 }
329 // aura can be removed in Unit::_AddAura call
330 if (aura->IsRemoved())
331 return NULL;
332 return aura;
333}

335Aura::Aura(SpellInfo const* spellproto, WorldObject* owner, Unit* caster, Item* castItem, ObjectGuid casterGUID) :
336m_spellInfo(spellproto), m_casterGuid(casterGUID ? casterGUID : caster->GetGUID()),
337m_castItemGuid(castItem ? castItem->GetGUID() : ObjectGuid::Empty), m_applyTime(time(NULL)),
338m_owner(owner), m_timeCla(0), m_updateTargetMapInterval(0),
339m_casterLevel(caster ? caster->getLevel() : m_spellInfo->SpellLevel), m_procCharges(0), m_stackAmount(1),
340m_isRemoved(false), m_isSingleTarget(false), m_isUsingCharges(false), m_dropEvent(nullptr)
341{
342 if (m_spellInfo->ManaPerSecond || m_spellInfo->ManaPerSecondPerLevel)
343 m_timeCla = 1 * IN_MILLISECONDS;
344
345 m_maxDuration = CalcMaxDuration(caster);
346 m_duration = m_maxDuration;
347 m_procCharges = CalcMaxCharges(caster);
348 m_isUsingCharges = m_procCharges != 0;
349 memset(m_effects, 0, sizeof(m_effects));
350 // m_casterLevel = cast item level/caster level, caster level should be saved to db, confirmed with sniffs
351}

353AuraScript* Aura::GetScriptByName(std::string const& scriptName) const
354{
355 for (std::list<AuraScript*>::const_iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); itr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++itr)
356 if ((*itr)->_GetScriptName()->compare(scriptName) == 0)
357 return *itr;
358 return NULL;
359}
360
361void Aura::_InitEffects(uint8 effMask, Unit* caster, int32 *baseAmount)
362{
363 // shouldn't be in constructor - functions in AuraEffect::AuraEffect use polymorphism
364 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
365 {
366 if (effMask & (uint8(1) << i))
367 m_effects[i] = new AuraEffect(this, i, baseAmount ? baseAmount + i : NULL, caster);
368 else
369 m_effects[i] = NULL;
370 }
371}
372
373Aura::~Aura()
374{
375 // unload scripts
376 while (!m_loadedScripts.empty())
377 {
378 std::list<AuraScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin();
379 (*itr)->_Unload();
380 delete (*itr);
381 m_loadedScripts.erase(itr);
382 }
383
384 // free effects memory
385 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
386 delete m_effects[i];
387
388 ASSERT(m_applications.empty());
389 _DeleteRemovedApplications();
390}

407void Aura::_ApplyForTarget(Unit* target, Unit* caster, AuraApplication * auraApp)
408{
409 ASSERT(target);
410 ASSERT(auraApp);
411 // aura mustn't be already applied on target
412 ASSERT (!IsAppliedOnTarget(target->GetGUID()) && "Aura::_ApplyForTarget: aura musn't be already applied on target");
413
414 m_applications[target->GetGUID()] = auraApp;
415
416 // set infinity cooldown state for spells
417 if (caster && caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
418 {
419 if (m_spellInfo->IsCooldownStartedOnEvent())
420 {
421 Item* castItem = m_castItemGuid ? caster->ToPlayer()->GetItemByGuid(m_castItemGuid) : NULL;
422 caster->GetSpellHistory()->StartCooldown(m_spellInfo, castItem ? castItem->GetEntry() : 0, nullptr, true);
423 }
424 }
425}
426
427void Aura::_UnapplyForTarget(Unit* target, Unit* caster, AuraApplication * auraApp)
428{
429 ASSERT(target);
430 ASSERT(auraApp->GetRemoveMode());
431 ASSERT(auraApp);
432
433 ApplicationMap::iterator itr = m_applications.find(target->GetGUID());
434
435 /// @todo Figure out why this happens
436 if (itr == m_applications.end())
437 {
438 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Aura::_UnapplyForTarget, target:%u, caster:%u, spell:%u was not found in owners application map!",
439 target->GetGUID().GetCounter(), caster ? caster->GetGUID().GetCounter() : 0, auraApp->GetBase()->GetSpellInfo()->Id);
440 ABORT();
441 }
442
443 // aura has to be already applied
444 ASSERT(itr->second == auraApp);
445 m_applications.erase(itr);
446
447 m_removedApplications.push_back(auraApp);
448
449 // reset cooldown state for spells
450 if (caster && GetSpellInfo()->IsCooldownStartedOnEvent())
451 // note: item based cooldowns and cooldown spell mods with charges ignored (unknown existed cases)
452 caster->GetSpellHistory()->SendCooldownEvent(GetSpellInfo());
453}

455// removes aura from all targets
456// and marks aura as removed
457void Aura::_Remove(AuraRemoveMode removeMode)
458{
459 ASSERT (!m_isRemoved);
460 m_isRemoved = true;
461 ApplicationMap::iterator appItr = m_applications.begin();
462 for (appItr = m_applications.begin(); appItr != m_applications.end();)
463 {
464 AuraApplication * aurApp = appItr->second;
465 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
466 target->_UnapplyAura(aurApp, removeMode);
467 appItr = m_applications.begin();
468 }
469
470 if (m_dropEvent)
471 {
472 m_dropEvent->to_Abort = true;
473 m_dropEvent = nullptr;
474 }
475}
476
477void Aura::UpdateTargetMap(Unit* caster, bool apply)
478{
479 if (IsRemoved())
480 return;
481
482 m_updateTargetMapInterval = UPDATE_TARGET_MAP_INTERVAL;
483
484 // fill up to date target list
485 // target, effMask
486 std::map<Unit*, uint8> targets;
487
488 FillTargetMap(targets, caster);
489
490 UnitList targetsToRemove;
491
492 // mark all auras as ready to remove
493 for (ApplicationMap::iterator appIter = m_applications.begin(); appIter != m_applications.end();++appIter)
494 {
495 std::map<Unit*, uint8>::iterator existing = targets.find(appIter->second->GetTarget());
496 // not found in current area - remove the aura
497 if (existing == targets.end())
498 targetsToRemove.push_back(appIter->second->GetTarget());
499 else
500 {
501 // needs readding - remove now, will be applied in next update cycle
502 // (dbcs do not have auras which apply on same type of targets but have different radius, so this is not really needed)
503 if (appIter->second->GetEffectMask() != existing->second || !CanBeAppliedOn(existing->first))
504 targetsToRemove.push_back(appIter->second->GetTarget());
505 // nothing todo - aura already applied
506 // remove from auras to register list
507 targets.erase(existing);
508 }
509 }
510
511 // register auras for units
512 for (std::map<Unit*, uint8>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr!= targets.end();)
513 {
514 // aura mustn't be already applied on target
515 if (AuraApplication * aurApp = GetApplicationOfTarget(itr->first->GetGUID()))
516 {
517 // the core created 2 different units with same guid
518 // this is a major failue, which i can't fix right now
519 // let's remove one unit from aura list
520 // this may cause area aura "bouncing" between 2 units after each update
521 // but because we know the reason of a crash we can remove the assertion for now
522 if (aurApp->GetTarget() != itr->first)
523 {
524 // remove from auras to register list
525 targets.erase(itr++);
526 continue;
527 }
528 else
529 {
530 // ok, we have one unit twice in target map (impossible, but...)
531 ABORT();
532 }
533 }
534
535 bool addUnit = true;
536 // check target immunities
537 for (uint8 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
538 {
539 if (itr->first->IsImmunedToSpellEffect(GetSpellInfo(), effIndex))
540 itr->second &= ~(1 << effIndex);
541 }
542 if (!itr->second
543 || itr->first->IsImmunedToSpell(GetSpellInfo())
544 || !CanBeAppliedOn(itr->first))
545 addUnit = false;
546
547 if (addUnit && !itr->first->IsHighestExclusiveAura(this, true))
548 addUnit = false;
549
550 if (addUnit)
551 {
552 // persistent area aura does not hit flying targets
553 if (GetType() == DYNOBJ_AURA_TYPE)
554 {
555 if (itr->first->IsInFlight())
556 addUnit = false;
557 }
558 // unit auras can not stack with each other
559 else // (GetType() == UNIT_AURA_TYPE)
560 {
561 // Allow to remove by stack when aura is going to be applied on owner
562 if (itr->first != GetOwner())
563 {
564 // check if not stacking aura already on target
565 // this one prevents unwanted usefull buff loss because of stacking and prevents overriding auras periodicaly by 2 near area aura owners
566 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::iterator iter = itr->first->GetAppliedAuras().begin(); iter != itr->first->GetAppliedAuras().end(); ++iter)
567 {
568 Aura const* aura = iter->second->GetBase();
569 if (!CanStackWith(aura))
570 {
571 addUnit = false;
572 break;
573 }
574 }
575 }
576 }
577 }
578 if (!addUnit)
579 targets.erase(itr++);
580 else
581 {
582 // owner has to be in world, or effect has to be applied to self
583 if (!GetOwner()->IsSelfOrInSameMap(itr->first))
584 {
585 /// @todo There is a crash caused by shadowfiend load addon
586 TC_LOG_FATAL("spells", "Aura %u: Owner %s (map %u) is not in the same map as target %s (map %u).", GetSpellInfo()->Id,
587 GetOwner()->GetName().c_str(), GetOwner()->IsInWorld() ? GetOwner()->GetMap()->GetId() : uint32(-1),
588 itr->first->GetName().c_str(), itr->first->IsInWorld() ? itr->first->GetMap()->GetId() : uint32(-1));
589 ABORT();
590 }
591 itr->first->_CreateAuraApplication(this, itr->second);
592 ++itr;
593 }
594 }
595
596 // remove auras from units no longer needing them
597 for (UnitList::iterator itr = targetsToRemove.begin(); itr != targetsToRemove.end();++itr)
598 if (AuraApplication * aurApp = GetApplicationOfTarget((*itr)->GetGUID()))
599 (*itr)->_UnapplyAura(aurApp, AURA_REMOVE_BY_DEFAULT);
600
601 if (!apply)
602 return;
603
604 // apply aura effects for units
605 for (std::map<Unit*, uint8>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr!= targets.end();++itr)
606 {
607 if (AuraApplication * aurApp = GetApplicationOfTarget(itr->first->GetGUID()))
608 {
609 // owner has to be in world, or effect has to be applied to self
610 ASSERT((!GetOwner()->IsInWorld() && GetOwner() == itr->first) || GetOwner()->IsInMap(itr->first));
611 itr->first->_ApplyAura(aurApp, itr->second);
612 }
613 }
614}
615
616// targets have to be registered and not have effect applied yet to use this function
617void Aura::_ApplyEffectForTargets(uint8 effIndex)
618{
619 // prepare list of aura targets
620 UnitList targetList;
621 for (ApplicationMap::iterator appIter = m_applications.begin(); appIter != m_applications.end(); ++appIter)
622 {
623 if ((appIter->second->GetEffectsToApply() & (1<<effIndex)) && !appIter->second->HasEffect(effIndex))
624 targetList.push_back(appIter->second->GetTarget());
625 }
626
627 // apply effect to targets
628 for (UnitList::iterator itr = targetList.begin(); itr != targetList.end(); ++itr)
629 {
630 if (GetApplicationOfTarget((*itr)->GetGUID()))
631 {
632 // owner has to be in world, or effect has to be applied to self
633 ASSERT((!GetOwner()->IsInWorld() && GetOwner() == *itr) || GetOwner()->IsInMap(*itr));
634 (*itr)->_ApplyAuraEffect(this, effIndex);
635 }
636 }
637}
638void Aura::UpdateOwner(uint32 diff, WorldObject* owner)
639{
640 ASSERT(owner == m_owner);
641
642 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
643 // Apply spellmods for channeled auras
644 // used for example when triggered spell of spell:10 is modded
645 Spell* modSpell = NULL;
646 Player* modOwner = NULL;
647 if (caster)
648 {
649 modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner();
650 if (modOwner)
651 {
652 modSpell = modOwner->FindCurrentSpellBySpellId(GetId());
653 if (modSpell)
654 modOwner->SetSpellModTakingSpell(modSpell, true);
655 }
656 }
657
658 Update(diff, caster);
659
660 if (m_updateTargetMapInterval <= int32(diff))
661 UpdateTargetMap(caster);
662 else
663 m_updateTargetMapInterval -= diff;
664
665 // update aura effects
666 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
667 if (m_effects[i])
668 m_effects[i]->Update(diff, caster);
669
670 // remove spellmods after effects update
671 if (modSpell)
672 modOwner->SetSpellModTakingSpell(modSpell, false);
673
674 _DeleteRemovedApplications();
675}
676
677void Aura::Update(uint32 diff, Unit* caster)
678{
679 if (m_duration > 0)
680 {
681 m_duration -= diff;
682 if (m_duration < 0)
683 m_duration = 0;
684
685 // handle manaPerSecond/manaPerSecondPerLevel
686 if (m_timeCla)
687 {
688 if (m_timeCla > int32(diff))
689 m_timeCla -= diff;
690 else if (caster)
691 {
692 if (int32 manaPerSecond = m_spellInfo->ManaPerSecond + m_spellInfo->ManaPerSecondPerLevel * caster->getLevel())
693 {
694 m_timeCla += 1000 - diff;
695
696 Powers powertype = Powers(m_spellInfo->PowerType);
697 if (powertype == POWER_HEALTH)
698 {
699 if (int32(caster->GetHealth()) > manaPerSecond)
700 caster->ModifyHealth(-manaPerSecond);
701 else
702 Remove();
703 }
704 else if (int32(caster->GetPower(powertype)) >= manaPerSecond)
705 caster->ModifyPower(powertype, -manaPerSecond);
706 else
707 Remove();
708 }
709 }
710 }
711 }
712}
713
714int32 Aura::CalcMaxDuration(Unit* caster) const
715{
716 Player* modOwner = NULL;
717 int32 maxDuration;
718
719 if (caster)
720 {
721 modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner();
722 maxDuration = caster->CalcSpellDuration(m_spellInfo);
723 }
724 else
725 maxDuration = m_spellInfo->GetDuration();
726
727 if (IsPassive() && !m_spellInfo->DurationEntry)
728 maxDuration = -1;
729
730 // IsPermanent() checks max duration (which we are supposed to calculate here)
731 if (maxDuration != -1 && modOwner)
732 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(GetId(), SPELLMOD_DURATION, maxDuration);
733
734 return maxDuration;
735}

737void Aura::SetDuration(int32 duration, bool withMods)
738{
739 if (withMods)
740 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
741 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
742 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(GetId(), SPELLMOD_DURATION, duration);
743
744 m_duration = duration;
745 SetNeedClientUpdateForTargets();
746}
747
748void Aura::RefreshDuration(bool withMods)
749{
750 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
751 if (withMods && caster)
752 {
753 int32 duration = m_spellInfo->GetMaxDuration();
754 // Calculate duration of periodics affected by haste.
755 if (caster->HasAuraTypeWithAffectMask(SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HASTE, m_spellInfo) || m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_HASTE_AFFECT_DURATION))
756 duration = int32(duration * caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED));
757
758 SetMaxDuration(duration);
759 SetDuration(duration);
760 }
761 else
762 SetDuration(GetMaxDuration());
763
764 if (m_spellInfo->ManaPerSecond || m_spellInfo->ManaPerSecondPerLevel)
765 m_timeCla = 1 * IN_MILLISECONDS;
766}

768void Aura::RefreshTimers()
769{
770 m_maxDuration = CalcMaxDuration();
771 RefreshDuration();
772 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
773 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
774 if (HasEffect(i))
775 GetEffect(i)->CalculatePeriodic(caster, false, false);
776}

800
801bool Aura::ModCharges(int32 num, AuraRemoveMode removeMode)
802{
803 if (IsUsingCharges())
804 {
805 int32 charges = m_procCharges + num;
806 int32 maxCharges = CalcMaxCharges();
807
808 // limit charges (only on charges increase, charges may be changed manually)
809 if ((num > 0) && (charges > int32(maxCharges)))
810 charges = maxCharges;
811 // we're out of charges, remove
812 else if (charges <= 0)
813 {
814 Remove(removeMode);
815 return true;
816 }
817
818 SetCharges(charges);
819 }
820
821 return false;
822}
823
824void Aura::ModChargesDelayed(int32 num, AuraRemoveMode removeMode)
825{
826 m_dropEvent = nullptr;
827 ModCharges(num, removeMode);
828}
829
830void Aura::DropChargeDelayed(uint32 delay, AuraRemoveMode removeMode)
831{
832 // aura is already during delayed charge drop
833 if (m_dropEvent)
834 return;
835 // only units have events
836 Unit* owner = m_owner->ToUnit();
837 if (!owner)
838 return;
839
840 m_dropEvent = new ChargeDropEvent(this, removeMode);
841 owner->m_Events.AddEvent(m_dropEvent, owner->m_Events.CalculateTime(delay));
842}
843
844void Aura::SetStackAmount(uint8 stackAmount)
845{
846 m_stackAmount = stackAmount;
847 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
848
849 std::list<AuraApplication*> applications;
850 GetApplicationList(applications);
851
852 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = applications.begin(); apptItr != applications.end(); ++apptItr)
853 if (!(*apptItr)->GetRemoveMode())
854 HandleAuraSpecificMods(*apptItr, caster, false, true);
855
856 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
857 if (HasEffect(i))
858 m_effects[i]->ChangeAmount(m_effects[i]->CalculateAmount(caster), false, true);
859
860 for (std::list<AuraApplication*>::const_iterator apptItr = applications.begin(); apptItr != applications.end(); ++apptItr)
861 if (!(*apptItr)->GetRemoveMode())
862 {
863 HandleAuraSpecificMods(*apptItr, caster, true, true);
864 HandleAuraSpecificPeriodics(*apptItr, caster);
865 }
866
867 SetNeedClientUpdateForTargets();
868}
869
870bool Aura::ModStackAmount(int32 num, AuraRemoveMode removeMode)
871{
872 int32 stackAmount = m_stackAmount + num;
873
874 // limit the stack amount (only on stack increase, stack amount may be changed manually)
875 if ((num > 0) && (stackAmount > int32(m_spellInfo->StackAmount)))
876 {
877 // not stackable aura - set stack amount to 1
878 if (!m_spellInfo->StackAmount)
879 stackAmount = 1;
880 else
881 stackAmount = m_spellInfo->StackAmount;
882 }
883 // we're out of stacks, remove
884 else if (stackAmount <= 0)
885 {
886 Remove(removeMode);
887 return true;
888 }
889
890 bool refresh = stackAmount >= GetStackAmount();
891
892 // Update stack amount
893 SetStackAmount(stackAmount);
894
895 if (refresh)
896 {
897 RefreshSpellMods();
898 RefreshTimers();
899
900 // reset charges
901 SetCharges(CalcMaxCharges());
902 // FIXME: not a best way to synchronize charges, but works
903 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
904 if (AuraEffect* aurEff = GetEffect(i))
905 if (aurEff->GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_ADD_FLAT_MODIFIER || aurEff->GetAuraType() == SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER)
906 if (SpellModifier* mod = aurEff->GetSpellModifier())
907 mod->charges = GetCharges();
908 }
909
910 SetNeedClientUpdateForTargets();
911 return false;
912}

916 for (Aura::ApplicationMap::const_iterator appIter = m_applications.begin(); appIter != m_applications.end(); ++appIter)
917 if (Player* player = appIter->second->GetTarget()->ToPlayer())
918 player->RestoreAllSpellMods(0, this);
919}

949
950bool Aura::CanBeSaved() const
951{
952 if (IsPassive())
953 return false;
954
955 if (GetCasterGUID() != GetOwner()->GetGUID())
956 if (GetSpellInfo()->IsSingleTarget())
957 return false;
958
959 // Can't be saved - aura handler relies on calculated amount and changes it
960 if (HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_CONVERT_RUNE))
961 return false;
962
963 // No point in saving this, since the stable dialog can't be open on aura load anyway.
964 if (HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_OPEN_STABLE))
965 return false;
966
967 // Can't save vehicle auras, it requires both caster & target to be in world
968 if (HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE))
969 return false;
970
971 // Incanter's Absorbtion - considering the minimal duration and problems with aura stacking
972 // we skip saving this aura
973 // Also for some reason other auras put as MultiSlot crash core on keeping them after restart,
974 // so put here only these for which you are sure they get removed
975 switch (GetId())
976 {
977 case 44413: // Incanter's Absorption
978 case 40075: // Fel Flak Fire
979 case 55849: // Power Spark
980 return false;
981 break;
982 }
983
984 // don't save auras removed by proc system
985 if (IsUsingCharges() && !GetCharges())
986 return false;
987
988 return true;
989}

991bool Aura::CanBeSentToClient() const
992{
993 return !IsPassive() || GetSpellInfo()->HasAreaAuraEffect() || HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_ABILITY_IGNORE_AURASTATE);
994}
995
996bool Aura::IsSingleTargetWith(Aura const* aura) const
997{
998 // Same spell?
999 if (GetSpellInfo()->IsRankOf(aura->GetSpellInfo()))
1000 return true;
1001
1002 SpellSpecificType spec = GetSpellInfo()->GetSpellSpecific();
1003 // spell with single target specific types
1004 switch (spec)
1005 {
1006 case SPELL_SPECIFIC_JUDGEMENT:
1007 case SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_POLYMORPH:
1008 if (aura->GetSpellInfo()->GetSpellSpecific() == spec)
1009 return true;
1010 break;
1011 default:
1012 break;
1013 }
1014
1015 if (HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE) && aura->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE))
1016 return true;
1017
1018 return false;
1019}

1030int32 Aura::CalcDispelChance(Unit* auraTarget, bool offensive) const
1031{
1032 // we assume that aura dispel chance is 100% on start
1033 // need formula for level difference based chance
1034 int32 resistChance = 0;
1035
1036 // Apply dispel mod from aura caster
1037 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
1038 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1039 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(GetId(), SPELLMOD_RESIST_DISPEL_CHANCE, resistChance);
1040
1041 // Dispel resistance from target SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISPEL_RESIST
1042 // Only affects offensive dispels
1043 if (offensive && auraTarget)
1044 resistChance += auraTarget->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISPEL_RESIST);
1045
1046 RoundToInterval(resistChance, 0, 100);
1047 return 100 - resistChance;
1048}

1110
1111// trigger effects on real aura apply/remove
1112void Aura::HandleAuraSpecificMods(AuraApplication const* aurApp, Unit* caster, bool apply, bool onReapply)
1113{
1114 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1115 AuraRemoveMode removeMode = aurApp->GetRemoveMode();
1116 // handle spell_area table
1117 SpellAreaForAreaMapBounds saBounds = sSpellMgr->GetSpellAreaForAuraMapBounds(GetId());
1118 if (saBounds.first != saBounds.second)
1119 {
1120 uint32 zone, area;
1121 target->GetZoneAndAreaId(zone, area);
1122
1123 for (SpellAreaForAreaMap::const_iterator itr = saBounds.first; itr != saBounds.second; ++itr)
1124 {
1125 // some auras remove at aura remove
1126 if (!itr->second->IsFitToRequirements(target->ToPlayer(), zone, area))
1127 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(itr->second->spellId);
1128 // some auras applied at aura apply
1129 else if (itr->second->autocast)
1130 {
1131 if (!target->HasAura(itr->second->spellId))
1132 target->CastSpell(target, itr->second->spellId, true);
1133 }
1134 }
1135 }
1136
1137 // handle spell_linked_spell table
1138 if (!onReapply)
1139 {
1140 // apply linked auras
1141 if (apply)
1142 {
1143 if (std::vector<int32> const* spellTriggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(GetId() + SPELL_LINK_AURA))
1144 {
1145 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator itr = spellTriggered->begin(); itr != spellTriggered->end(); ++itr)
1146 {
1147 if (*itr < 0)
1148 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_ID, -(*itr), true);
1149 else if (caster)
1150 caster->AddAura(*itr, target);
1151 }
1152 }
1153 }
1154 else
1155 {
1156 // remove linked auras
1157 if (std::vector<int32> const* spellTriggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(-(int32)GetId()))
1158 {
1159 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator itr = spellTriggered->begin(); itr != spellTriggered->end(); ++itr)
1160 {
1161 if (*itr < 0)
1162 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(-(*itr));
1163 else if (removeMode != AURA_REMOVE_BY_DEATH)
1164 target->CastSpell(target, *itr, true, NULL, NULL, GetCasterGUID());
1165 }
1166 }
1167 if (std::vector<int32> const* spellTriggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(GetId() + SPELL_LINK_AURA))
1168 {
1169 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator itr = spellTriggered->begin(); itr != spellTriggered->end(); ++itr)
1170 {
1171 if (*itr < 0)
1172 target->ApplySpellImmune(GetId(), IMMUNITY_ID, -(*itr), false);
1173 else
1174 target->RemoveAura(*itr, GetCasterGUID(), 0, removeMode);
1175 }
1176 }
1177 }
1178 }
1179 else if (apply)
1180 {
1181 // modify stack amount of linked auras
1182 if (std::vector<int32> const* spellTriggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(GetId() + SPELL_LINK_AURA))
1183 {
1184 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator itr = spellTriggered->begin(); itr != spellTriggered->end(); ++itr)
1185 if (*itr > 0)
1186 if (Aura* triggeredAura = target->GetAura(*itr, GetCasterGUID()))
1187 triggeredAura->ModStackAmount(GetStackAmount() - triggeredAura->GetStackAmount());
1188 }
1189 }
1190
1191 // mods at aura apply
1192 if (apply)
1193 {
1194 switch (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName)
1195 {
1196 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
1197 switch (GetId())
1198 {
1199 case 32474: // Buffeting Winds of Susurrus
1200 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1201 target->ToPlayer()->ActivateTaxiPathTo(506, GetId());
1202 break;
1203 case 33572: // Gronn Lord's Grasp, becomes stoned
1204 if (GetStackAmount() >= 5 && !target->HasAura(33652))
1205 target->CastSpell(target, 33652, true);
1206 break;
1207 case 50836: //Petrifying Grip, becomes stoned
1208 if (GetStackAmount() >= 5 && !target->HasAura(50812))
1209 target->CastSpell(target, 50812, true);
1210 break;
1211 case 60970: // Heroic Fury (remove Intercept cooldown)
1212 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1213 target->GetSpellHistory()->ResetCooldown(20252, true);
1214 break;
1215 }
1216 break;
1217 case SPELLFAMILY_DRUID:
1218 if (!caster)
1219 break;
1220 // Rejuvenation
1221 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x10 && GetEffect(EFFECT_0))
1222 {
1223 // Druid T8 Restoration 4P Bonus
1224 if (caster->HasAura(64760))
1225 {
1226 int32 heal = GetEffect(EFFECT_0)->GetAmount();
1227 caster->CastCustomSpell(target, 64801, &heal, NULL, NULL, true, NULL, GetEffect(EFFECT_0));
1228 }
1229 }
1230 break;
1231 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
1232 if (!caster)
1233 break;
1234 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000001 && GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00000008)
1235 {
1236 // Glyph of Fireball
1237 if (caster->HasAura(56368))
1238 SetDuration(0);
1239 }
1240 else if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000020 && GetSpellInfo()->SpellVisual[0] == 13)
1241 {
1242 // Glyph of Frostbolt
1243 if (caster->HasAura(56370))
1244 SetDuration(0);
1245 }
1246 /// @todo This should be moved to similar function in spell::hit
1247 else if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x01000000)
1248 {
1249 // Polymorph Sound - Sheep && Penguin
1250 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellIconID == 82 && GetSpellInfo()->SpellVisual[0] == 12978)
1251 {
1252 // Glyph of the Penguin
1253 if (caster->HasAura(52648))
1254 caster->CastSpell(target, 61635, true);
1255 else
1256 caster->CastSpell(target, 61634, true);
1257 }
1258 }
1259 switch (GetId())
1260 {
1261 case 12536: // Clearcasting
1262 case 12043: // Presence of Mind
1263 // Arcane Potency
1264 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = caster->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_DUMMY, SPELLFAMILY_MAGE, 2120, 0))
1265 {
1266 uint32 spellId = 0;
1267
1268 switch (aurEff->GetId())
1269 {
1270 case 31571: spellId = 57529; break;
1271 case 31572: spellId = 57531; break;
1272 default:
1273 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Aura::HandleAuraSpecificMods: Unknown rank of Arcane Potency (%d) found", aurEff->GetId());
1274 }
1275 if (spellId)
1276 caster->CastSpell(caster, spellId, true);
1277 }
1278 break;
1279 case 44544: // Fingers of Frost
1280 {
1281 // See if we already have the indicator aura. If not, create one.
1282 if (Aura* aur = target->GetAura(74396))
1283 {
1284 // Aura already there. Refresh duration and set original charges
1285 aur->SetCharges(2);
1286 aur->RefreshDuration();
1287 }
1288 else
1289 target->AddAura(74396, target);
1290 }
1291 default:
1292 break;
1293 }
1294 break;
1295 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
1296 if (!caster)
1297 break;
1298 // Devouring Plague
1299 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x02000000 && GetEffect(0))
1300 {
1301 // Improved Devouring Plague
1302 if (AuraEffect const* aurEff = caster->GetDummyAuraEffect(SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST, 3790, 1))
1303 {
1304 uint32 damage = caster->SpellDamageBonusDone(target, GetSpellInfo(), GetEffect(0)->GetAmount(), DOT);
1305 damage *= caster->SpellDamagePctDone(target, GetSpellInfo(), SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE);
1306 damage = target->SpellDamageBonusTaken(caster, GetSpellInfo(), damage, DOT);
1307 int32 basepoints0 = aurEff->GetAmount() * GetEffect(0)->GetTotalTicks() * int32(damage) / 100;
1308 int32 heal = int32(CalculatePct(basepoints0, 15));
1309
1310 caster->CastCustomSpell(target, 63675, &basepoints0, NULL, NULL, true, NULL, GetEffect(0));
1311 caster->CastCustomSpell(caster, 75999, &heal, NULL, NULL, true, NULL, GetEffect(0));
1312 }
1313 }
1314 // Power Word: Shield
1315 else if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x1 && m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x400 && GetEffect(0))
1316 {
1317 // Glyph of Power Word: Shield
1318 if (AuraEffect* glyph = caster->GetAuraEffect(55672, 0))
1319 {
1320 // instantly heal m_amount% of the absorb-value
1321 int32 heal = glyph->GetAmount() * GetEffect(0)->GetAmount()/100;
1322 caster->CastCustomSpell(GetUnitOwner(), 56160, &heal, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, GetEffect(0));
1323 }
1324 }
1325 break;
1326 case SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE:
1327 // Sprint (skip non player cast spells by category)
1328 if (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x40 && GetSpellInfo()->GetCategory() == 44)

1662void Aura::HandleAuraSpecificPeriodics(AuraApplication const* aurApp, Unit* caster)
1663{
1664 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1665
1666 if (!caster || aurApp->GetRemoveMode())
1667 return;
1668
1669 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1670 {
1671 if (!HasEffect(i))
1672 continue;
1673
1674 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsAreaAuraEffect() || m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA))
1675 continue;
1676
1677 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
1678 {
1679 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
1680 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
1681 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
1682 {
1683 AuraEffect* aurEff = GetEffect(i);
1684
1685 aurEff->SetDonePct(caster->SpellDamagePctDone(target, m_spellInfo, DOT));
1686 aurEff->SetBonusAmount(caster->SpellDamageBonusDone(target, m_spellInfo, 0, DOT, GetStackAmount()));
1687 aurEff->SetCritChance(caster->GetUnitSpellCriticalChance(target, m_spellInfo, m_spellInfo->GetSchoolMask()));
1688 break;
1689 }
1690 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
1691 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
1692 {
1693 AuraEffect* aurEff = GetEffect(i);
1694
1695 aurEff->SetDonePct(caster->SpellHealingPctDone(target, m_spellInfo));
1696 aurEff->SetBonusAmount(caster->SpellHealingBonusDone(target, m_spellInfo, 0, DOT, GetStackAmount()));
1697 aurEff->SetCritChance(caster->GetUnitSpellCriticalChance(target, m_spellInfo, m_spellInfo->GetSchoolMask()));
1698 break;
1699 }
1700 default:
1701 break;
1702 }
1703 }
1704}

1706bool Aura::CanBeAppliedOn(Unit* target)
1707{
1708 // unit not in world or during remove from world
1709 if (!target->IsInWorld() || target->IsDuringRemoveFromWorld())
1710 {
1711 // area auras mustn't be applied
1712 if (GetOwner() != target)
1713 return false;
1714 // do not apply non-selfcast single target auras
1715 if (GetCasterGUID() != GetOwner()->GetGUID() && GetSpellInfo()->IsSingleTarget())
1716 return false;
1717 return true;
1718 }
1719 else
1720 return CheckAreaTarget(target);
1721}

1724{
1725 return CallScriptCheckAreaTargetHandlers(target);

1727
1728bool Aura::CanStackWith(Aura const* existingAura) const
1729{
1730 // Can stack with self
1731 if (this == existingAura)
1732 return true;
1733
1734 // Dynobj auras always stack
1735 if (GetType() == DYNOBJ_AURA_TYPE || existingAura->GetType() == DYNOBJ_AURA_TYPE)
1736 return true;
1737
1738 SpellInfo const* existingSpellInfo = existingAura->GetSpellInfo();
1739 bool sameCaster = GetCasterGUID() == existingAura->GetCasterGUID();
1740
1741 // passive auras don't stack with another rank of the spell cast by same caster
1742 if (IsPassive() && sameCaster && m_spellInfo->IsDifferentRankOf(existingSpellInfo))
1743 return false;
1744
1745 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1746 {
1747 // prevent remove triggering aura by triggered aura
1748 if (existingSpellInfo->Effects[i].TriggerSpell == GetId()
1749 // prevent remove triggered aura by triggering aura refresh
1750 || m_spellInfo->Effects[i].TriggerSpell == existingAura->GetId())
1751 return true;
1752 }
1753
1754 // Check for custom server setting to allow tracking both Herbs and Minerals
1755 // Note: The following are client limitations and cannot be coded for:
1756 // * The minimap tracking icon will display whichever skill is activated second
1757 // * The minimap tracking list will only show a check mark next to the last skill activated
1758 // Sometimes this bugs out and doesn't switch the check mark. It has no effect on the actual tracking though.
1759 // * The minimap dots are yellow for both resources
1760 if (m_spellInfo->HasAura(SPELL_AURA_TRACK_RESOURCES) && existingSpellInfo->HasAura(SPELL_AURA_TRACK_RESOURCES))
1761 return sWorld->getBoolConfig(CONFIG_ALLOW_TRACK_BOTH_RESOURCES);
1762
1763 // check spell specific stack rules
1764 if (m_spellInfo->IsAuraExclusiveBySpecificWith(existingSpellInfo)
1765 || (sameCaster && m_spellInfo->IsAuraExclusiveBySpecificPerCasterWith(existingSpellInfo)))
1766 return false;
1767
1768 // check spell group stack rules
1769 switch (sSpellMgr->CheckSpellGroupStackRules(m_spellInfo, existingSpellInfo))
1770 {
1771 case SPELL_GROUP_STACK_RULE_EXCLUSIVE:
1772 case SPELL_GROUP_STACK_RULE_EXCLUSIVE_HIGHEST: // if it reaches this point, existing aura is lower/equal
1773 return false;
1774 case SPELL_GROUP_STACK_RULE_EXCLUSIVE_FROM_SAME_CASTER:
1775 if (sameCaster)
1776 return false;
1777 break;
1778 case SPELL_GROUP_STACK_RULE_DEFAULT:
1779 case SPELL_GROUP_STACK_RULE_EXCLUSIVE_SAME_EFFECT:
1780 default:
1781 break;
1782 }
1783
1784 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName != existingSpellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
1785 return true;
1786
1787 if (!sameCaster)
1788 {
1789 // Channeled auras can stack if not forbidden by db or aura type
1790 if (existingAura->GetSpellInfo()->IsChanneled())
1791 return true;
1792
1793 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_STACK_FOR_DIFF_CASTERS))
1794 return true;
1795
1796 // check same periodic auras
1797 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1798 {
1799 switch (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
1800 {
1801 // DOT or HOT from different casters will stack
1802 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
1803 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
1804 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
1805 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
1806 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_ENERGIZE:
1807 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
1808 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
1809 case SPELL_AURA_POWER_BURN:
1810 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
1811 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
1812 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
1813 // periodic auras which target areas are not allowed to stack this way (replenishment for example)
1814 if (m_spellInfo->Effects[i].IsTargetingArea() || existingSpellInfo->Effects[i].IsTargetingArea())
1815 break;
1816 return true;
1817 default:
1818 break;
1819 }
1820 }
1821 }
1822
1823 if (HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE) && existingAura->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_CONTROL_VEHICLE))
1824 {
1825 Vehicle* veh = NULL;
1826 if (GetOwner()->ToUnit())
1827 veh = GetOwner()->ToUnit()->GetVehicleKit();
1828
1829 if (!veh) // We should probably just let it stack. Vehicle system will prevent undefined behaviour later
1830 return true;
1831
1832 if (!veh->GetAvailableSeatCount())
1833 return false; // No empty seat available
1834
1835 return true; // Empty seat available (skip rest)
1836 }
1837
1838 // spell of same spell rank chain
1839 if (m_spellInfo->IsRankOf(existingSpellInfo))
1840 {
1841 // don't allow passive area auras to stack
1842 if (m_spellInfo->IsMultiSlotAura() && !IsArea())
1843 return true;
1844 if (GetCastItemGUID() && existingAura->GetCastItemGUID())
1845 if (GetCastItemGUID() != existingAura->GetCastItemGUID() && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_ENCHANT_PROC))
1846 return true;
1847 // same spell with same caster should not stack
1848 return false;
1849 }
1850
1851 return true;
1852}

1869void Aura::PrepareProcToTrigger(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1870{
1871 bool prepare = CallScriptPrepareProcHandlers(aurApp, eventInfo);
1872 if (!prepare)
1873 return;
1874
1875 // take one charge, aura expiration will be handled in Aura::TriggerProcOnEvent (if needed)
1876 if (IsUsingCharges())
1877 {
1878 --m_procCharges;
1879 SetNeedClientUpdateForTargets();
1880 }
1881
1882 SpellProcEntry const* procEntry = sSpellMgr->GetSpellProcEntry(GetId());
1883
1884 ASSERT(procEntry);
1885
1886 // cooldowns should be added to the whole aura (see 51698 area aura)
1887 AddProcCooldown(procEntry->cooldown);
1888}
1889
1890bool Aura::IsProcTriggeredOnEvent(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo) const
1891{
1892 SpellProcEntry const* procEntry = sSpellMgr->GetSpellProcEntry(GetId());
1893 // only auras with spell proc entry can trigger proc
1894 if (!procEntry)
1895 return false;
1896
1897 // check if we have charges to proc with
1898 if (IsUsingCharges() && !GetCharges())
1899 return false;
1900
1901 // check proc cooldown
1902 if (IsProcOnCooldown())
1903 return false;
1904
1905 /// @todo
1906 // something about triggered spells triggering, and add extra attack effect
1907
1908 // do checks against db data
1909 if (!sSpellMgr->CanSpellTriggerProcOnEvent(*procEntry, eventInfo))
1910 return false;
1911
1912 // do checks using conditions table
1913 if (!sConditionMgr->IsObjectMeetingNotGroupedConditions(CONDITION_SOURCE_TYPE_SPELL_PROC, GetId(), eventInfo.GetActor(), eventInfo.GetActionTarget()))
1914 return false;
1915
1916 // AuraScript Hook
1917 bool check = const_cast<Aura*>(this)->CallScriptCheckProcHandlers(aurApp, eventInfo);
1918 if (!check)
1919 return false;
1920
1921 /// @todo
1922 // do allow additional requirements for procs
1923 // this is needed because this is the last moment in which you can prevent aura charge drop on proc
1924 // and possibly a way to prevent default checks (if there're going to be any)
1925
1926 // Check if current equipment meets aura requirements
1927 // do that only for passive spells
1928 /// @todo this needs to be unified for all kinds of auras
1929 Unit* target = aurApp->GetTarget();
1930 if (IsPassive() && target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1931 {
1932 if (GetSpellInfo()->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON)
1933 {
1934 if (target->ToPlayer()->IsInFeralForm())
1935 return false;
1936
1937 if (eventInfo.GetDamageInfo())
1938 {
1939 WeaponAttackType attType = eventInfo.GetDamageInfo()->GetAttackType();
1940 Item* item = NULL;
1941 if (attType == BASE_ATTACK)
1942 item = target->ToPlayer()->GetUseableItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND);
1943 else if (attType == OFF_ATTACK)
1944 item = target->ToPlayer()->GetUseableItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND);
1945 else
1946 item = target->ToPlayer()->GetUseableItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED);
1947
1948 if (!item || item->IsBroken() || item->GetTemplate()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON || !((1<<item->GetTemplate()->SubClass) & GetSpellInfo()->EquippedItemSubClassMask))
1949 return false;
1950 }
1951 }
1952 else if (GetSpellInfo()->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR)
1953 {
1954 // Check if player is wearing shield
1955 Item* item = target->ToPlayer()->GetUseableItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND);
1956 if (!item || item->IsBroken() || item->GetTemplate()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR || !((1<<item->GetTemplate()->SubClass) & GetSpellInfo()->EquippedItemSubClassMask))
1957 return false;
1958 }
1959 }
1960
1961 return roll_chance_f(CalcProcChance(*procEntry, eventInfo));
1962}
1963
1964float Aura::CalcProcChance(SpellProcEntry const& procEntry, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo) const
1965{
1966 float chance = procEntry.chance;
1967 // calculate chances depending on unit with caster's data
1968 // so talents modifying chances and judgements will have properly calculated proc chance
1969 if (Unit* caster = GetCaster())
1970 {
1971 // calculate ppm chance if present and we're using weapon
1972 if (eventInfo.GetDamageInfo() && procEntry.ratePerMinute != 0)
1973 {
1974 uint32 WeaponSpeed = caster->GetAttackTime(eventInfo.GetDamageInfo()->GetAttackType());
1975 chance = caster->GetPPMProcChance(WeaponSpeed, procEntry.ratePerMinute, GetSpellInfo());
1976 }
1977 // apply chance modifer aura, applies also to ppm chance (see improved judgement of light spell)
1978 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1979 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(GetId(), SPELLMOD_CHANCE_OF_SUCCESS, chance);
1980 }
1981 return chance;
1982}
1983
1984void Aura::TriggerProcOnEvent(AuraApplication* aurApp, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
1985{
1986 CallScriptProcHandlers(aurApp, eventInfo);
1987
1988 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1989 if (aurApp->HasEffect(i))
1990 // OnEffectProc / AfterEffectProc hooks handled in AuraEffect::HandleProc()
1991 GetEffect(i)->HandleProc(aurApp, eventInfo);
1992
1993 CallScriptAfterProcHandlers(aurApp, eventInfo);
1994
1995 // Remove aura if we've used last charge to proc
1996 if (IsUsingCharges() && !GetCharges())
1997 Remove();
1998}
1999
2000void Aura::_DeleteRemovedApplications()
2001{
2002 while (!m_removedApplications.empty())
2003 {
2004 delete m_removedApplications.front();
2005 m_removedApplications.pop_front();
2006 }
2007}

2009void Aura::LoadScripts()
2010{
2011 sScriptMgr->CreateAuraScripts(m_spellInfo->Id, m_loadedScripts);
2012 for (std::list<AuraScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); itr != m_loadedScripts.end();)
2013 {
2014 if (!(*itr)->_Load(this))
2015 {
2016 std::list<AuraScript*>::iterator bitr = itr;
2017 ++itr;
2018 delete (*bitr);
2019 m_loadedScripts.erase(bitr);
2020 continue;
2021 }
2022 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Aura::LoadScripts: Script `%s` for aura `%u` is loaded now", (*itr)->_GetScriptName()->c_str(), m_spellInfo->Id);
2023 (*itr)->Register();
2024 ++itr;
2025 }
2026}

2418void UnitAura::FillTargetMap(std::map<Unit*, uint8> & targets, Unit* caster)
2419{
2420 for (uint8 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
2421 {
2422 if (!HasEffect(effIndex))
2423 continue;
2424 UnitList targetList;
2425 // non-area aura
2426 if (GetSpellInfo()->Effects[effIndex].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2427 {
2428 targetList.push_back(GetUnitOwner());
2429 }
2430 else
2431 {
2432 float radius = GetSpellInfo()->Effects[effIndex].CalcRadius(caster);
2433
2434 if (!GetUnitOwner()->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ISOLATED))
2435 {
2436 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Effects[effIndex].Effect)
2437 {
2438 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_PARTY:
2439 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_RAID:
2440 {
2441 targetList.push_back(GetUnitOwner());
2442 Trinity::AnyGroupedUnitInObjectRangeCheck u_check(GetUnitOwner(), GetUnitOwner(), radius, GetSpellInfo()->Effects[effIndex].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_RAID);
2443 Trinity::UnitListSearcher<Trinity::AnyGroupedUnitInObjectRangeCheck> searcher(GetUnitOwner(), targetList, u_check);
2444 GetUnitOwner()->VisitNearbyObject(radius, searcher);
2445 break;
2446 }
2447 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_FRIEND:
2448 {
2449 targetList.push_back(GetUnitOwner());
2450 Trinity::AnyFriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck u_check(GetUnitOwner(), GetUnitOwner(), radius);
2451 Trinity::UnitListSearcher<Trinity::AnyFriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck> searcher(GetUnitOwner(), targetList, u_check);
2452 GetUnitOwner()->VisitNearbyObject(radius, searcher);
2453 break;
2454 }
2455 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_ENEMY:
2456 {
2457 Trinity::AnyAoETargetUnitInObjectRangeCheck u_check(GetUnitOwner(), GetUnitOwner(), radius); // No GetCharmer in searcher
2458 Trinity::UnitListSearcher<Trinity::AnyAoETargetUnitInObjectRangeCheck> searcher(GetUnitOwner(), targetList, u_check);
2459 GetUnitOwner()->VisitNearbyObject(radius, searcher);
2460 break;
2461 }
2462 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_PET:
2463 targetList.push_back(GetUnitOwner());
2464 // no break
2465 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_OWNER:
2466 {
2467 if (Unit* owner = GetUnitOwner()->GetCharmerOrOwner())
2468 if (GetUnitOwner()->IsWithinDistInMap(owner, radius))
2469 targetList.push_back(owner);
2470 break;
2471 }
2472 }
2473 }
2474 }
2475
2476 for (UnitList::iterator itr = targetList.begin(); itr!= targetList.end();++itr)
2477 {
2478 std::map<Unit*, uint8>::iterator existing = targets.find(*itr);
2479 if (existing != targets.end())
2480 existing->second |= 1<<effIndex;
2481 else
2482 targets[*itr] = 1<<effIndex;
2483 }
2484 }
2485}

2505void DynObjAura::FillTargetMap(std::map<Unit*, uint8> & targets, Unit* /*caster*/)
2506{
2507 Unit* dynObjOwnerCaster = GetDynobjOwner()->GetCaster();
2508 float radius = GetDynobjOwner()->GetRadius();
2509
2510 for (uint8 effIndex = 0; effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++effIndex)
2511 {
2512 if (!HasEffect(effIndex))
2513 continue;
2514 UnitList targetList;
2515 if (GetSpellInfo()->Effects[effIndex].TargetB.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ALLY
2516 || GetSpellInfo()->Effects[effIndex].TargetB.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_DEST_AREA_ALLY)
2517 {
2518 Trinity::AnyFriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck u_check(GetDynobjOwner(), dynObjOwnerCaster, radius);
2519 Trinity::UnitListSearcher<Trinity::AnyFriendlyUnitInObjectRangeCheck> searcher(GetDynobjOwner(), targetList, u_check);
2520 GetDynobjOwner()->VisitNearbyObject(radius, searcher);
2521 }
2522 else
2523 {
2524 Trinity::AnyAoETargetUnitInObjectRangeCheck u_check(GetDynobjOwner(), dynObjOwnerCaster, radius);
2525 Trinity::UnitListSearcher<Trinity::AnyAoETargetUnitInObjectRangeCheck> searcher(GetDynobjOwner(), targetList, u_check);
2526 GetDynobjOwner()->VisitNearbyObject(radius, searcher);
2527 }
2528
2529 for (UnitList::iterator itr = targetList.begin(); itr!= targetList.end();++itr)
2530 {
2531 std::map<Unit*, uint8>::iterator existing = targets.find(*itr);
2532 if (existing != targets.end())
2533 existing->second |= 1<<effIndex;
2534 else
2535 targets[*itr] = 1<<effIndex;
2536 }
2537 }
2538}
